<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="40" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,297]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,151,177]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Base of M complete; vein M 
<number box="[618,626,168,182]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40" value="2.0">2</number>
incomplete, anal lobe and alula lost; readily distinguished on basis of relatively large flagellomere 
<number box="[517,533,193,219]" pageId="6" pageNumber="40" value="1.0">1</number>
, which has an acute ventral margin. Arista dorsal. Sursylus simple (not multilobed), digitiform; postgonite long, apex slightly hooked; apical margin of hypandrium with pair of long thin lobes. In Lebanese amber.
</paragraph>
